notesStmt.note: Marginal notation from later readers throughout
Psalms 1-148 numbered in a later hand
Eighteenth-century printed prayers and litany on front and back end papers

msIdentifier.collection: John Frederick Lewis Collection of European Manuscripts

supportDesc.extent: i+175+i; 113 x 85 mm bound to 120 x 87 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto

layoutDesc.layout: Frame-ruled in ink; one column of 18 lines; written area: 83 x 60 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Three historiated initials; five-line puzzle initials in red and blue throughout; two-line pen-flourished initials in red and blue throughout; one-line initials in red or blue throughout; decorative line fillers in red or blue throughout
[Flyleaf 1 verso]Notation, "For Mr. Foggo with the kindest regards of his parishioner Caroline Countess Bouxhoevden, April 16 th 1856"; and "presented to W. W. Wiltbank Esqr. Octr 9 th 1893."
1rTen line historiated initial, initial B, King David and the Holy Spirit
53rSixteen line historiated initial Q, Archangel slaying dragon
105rTen line historiated initial, Initial D, Pope giving benediction

binding.p: Late 18th-century red morocco, gold stamped decoration on borders and spine; gilt edges; "PSALTERIUM" stamped on green morocco label on spine; marbled end papers

history.provenance: Unidentified 18th century armorial bookplate on inside of front cover; bookplate has the signature of Emile Gay and is dated 1821; on the verso of the front flyleaf is inscribed; "For Mr. Foggo with the kindest regards of his parishioner Caroline Countess Bouxhoevden, April 16th 1856" and "presented to W.W. Wiltbank Esqr. Octr 9th 1893." "XIII century" also written in pencil in Lewis's hand on the verso of the front flyleaf and again at the top of 1r

keywords.term: De Ricci, Seymour, with the assistance of W. J. Wilson, Census of Medieval and Renaissance Manuscripts in the United States and Canada, vol. 2 (New York,: H. W. Wilson, 1935-40), p. 2019, no. 23
